{"name":"Interrogation","permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.PNw3e4kuXZjUciXn"}},"content":"<p>System officers round up one of the PCs to question them about the crew&rsquo;s crimes. How did they manage to capture you? Either pay them off with 2 <strong>Cred</strong>, or they sweat it out of you (level 2 <strong>Harm</strong>) AND you tell them what they want to know (+2 <strong>Heat</strong> ). You can resist each of those consequences separately.</p>","_id":"5NdDWbDu3xmkXXLn"}
{"name":"Impounded","permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.IWtogoMn9M46LWP4"}},"content":"<p>Dock authorities impound your craft. Bribe dockworkers to lift the lockdown with 2 <strong>Cred</strong>, or steal your ship back. If you are not on a planet or station, you avoid entanglements right now.</p>","_id":"HKfLVHRPrjMO5qi6"}
{"name":"New \"Friends\"","permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.rBciFjAOP8pO4niq"}},"content":"<p>A neutral faction asks you to do a job that is either extra dangerous, pays little, or gathers more <strong>Heat</strong> than usual (GM&rsquo;s choice). Accept or lose a status with them.</p>\n<p>The GM should look at their faction goals for job prompts.</p>","_id":"HnxdZyllgq2Sbv3X"}
{"name":"Collectors","permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.Fg3HsbvwCRbSGbdq"}},"content":"<p>A collection agency claims part of your ship. Pay them 2 <strong>Cred</strong>, give them the components (remove a ship module), or make them leave another way.</p>","_id":"YzXh9sLukJQR8u3R"}
{"name":"Ur Field","permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.LaIM6d7Py6WOG2Zu"}},"content":"<p>The closest jumpgate calls to each of you in a language you cannot understand. Resist with <strong>Resolve</strong> or take level 1 <strong>Harm</strong> from the visions you cannot escape.</p>\n<p>What you choose to do with the visions is up to you. They end after you leave the system or the next downtime, whichever comes first.</p>","_id":"aslj0MhKSMxrcf9X"}
{"_id":"iP2JabMLeS3yrFD1","name":"Arrest","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.AuC8RSjETjJdvAOK"}},"content":"<p>A detective presents a case file of evidence to a judge, to begin prosecution of your crew. The system police send a detail to arrest you (a gang at least equal in <strong>scale</strong> to your <strong>Wanted Level</strong> or a ship of that Tier). Pay them off with <strong>Cred</strong> equal to your <strong>Wanted Level</strong> +3, hand someone over for arrest (this clears your <strong>Heat</strong> and <strong>Wanted Level</strong> in the system), or try to evade capture.</p>"}
{"name":"Bounty Hunter","permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.oKhxhbNS08oAsJ7k"}},"content":"<p>An enemy faction hires a bounty hunter. Fight, evade, or pay them off.&nbsp; If you have no faction with negative status, you avoid entanglements right now.</p>\n<p>Bounty hunters are strong fighters, with armor, drones, and weapons that grant them <strong>potency</strong> in combat. Base their Tier on the hiring faction and how angry they are. Pay them off with 3 <strong>Cred</strong>.</p>","_id":"iwND2KVIoa5z3gdO"}
{"name":"Cooperation","permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.qs6MZ60Fa7w9KYfW"}},"content":"<p>A faction you have +2 or +3 status with asks you for a &ldquo;favor.&rdquo; Agree to it or lose a status with them. If you don&rsquo;t have a +2 or +3 faction status, you avoid entanglements right now.</p>\n<p>The GM should look at the faction&rsquo;s goals for job prompts.</p>","_id":"mgoUhYt9kr0rCN7y"}
{"name":"Wanted Level 4","permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.rciMmrZ585vP1pWc"}},"content":"<p>Warship!</p>\n<p>The Governor sends a Legion or Malklaith warship to capture your ship. When you hit <strong>Wanted Level</strong> 4 in a system, the Governor&rsquo;s personal guard is sent out to bring you to justice, and you will have to find a way to get away. You cannot bribe them, and fighting them would be foolhardy. In any case, if you survive the encounter, your <strong>Wanted Level</strong> drops by 1 (resources for your pursuit aren&rsquo;t infinite).</p>\n<p>Generally the ship will be a well-armed frigate with a few personal fighters. You may want to consider repainting or modifying your ship, or getting fake papers and transponders to help shake similar experiences off your tail.</p>","_id":"npYCvTsMYoIEnl6X"}
{"name":"Pirates!","permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.nstag7t1WUhBqxTb"}},"content":"<p>Pirates attempt to take over your ship by force. Outrun, fight, or cut a deal. If you didn&rsquo;t use your ship at all on the last job, you avoid entanglements right now.</p>\n<p>This entanglement can happen while in flight between planets or systems, or on the way to or from a job.</p>","_id":"pv1KieJ826c5uTUP"}
{"name":"Reprisals","permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.NlZTR3MLtss1acl2"}},"content":"<p>An enemy faction moves against you or yours. Pay them 1 <strong>Cred </strong>per Tier, allow them to mess with you, or fight back. If you have no faction with negative status, you avoid entanglements right now.</p>","_id":"s5IoLw5f9o8OT2MA"}
{"name":"Out of Gas","permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.yrMieuZD98sc6vSi"}},"content":"<p>A piece of your ship fails catastrophically, damaging the system and rendering it inoperable until repaired. If you didn&rsquo;t use your ship at all on the last job, you avoid entanglements right now.</p>\n<p>This entanglement can happen while in flight between planets or systems, or on the way to or from a job. This failure means the whole system (for example, engines) can&rsquo;t be used. Who do you call for help and what will it cost you?</p>","_id":"vNqFmmIVFLHoHaRK"}
{"name":"Unquiet Black","permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.jZO37zioZJr3N2ai"}},"content":"<p>An alien or Way creature finds its way on board. Acquire the services of a mystic or exterminator to destroy or banish it, or deal with it yourself.</p>\n<p>Treat the magnitude (see page 278) of the Way creature as equal to the crew&rsquo;s <strong>Wanted Level</strong> in the system. Parasites, cargo you weren&rsquo;t told was alive, strange creatures hiding in unmapped lanes, and bizarre physics effects from using your jump drives way past capacity can all apply here.</p>","_id":"wyLno63260DGXUVt"}
{"name":"Ship Trouble","permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.rfr7C2v9WOcqe7rY"}},"content":"<p>A ship system acts up. Damage a system (the GM will tell you which).</p>\n<p>You may repair the system as normal, though you have to deal with the consequences of the damage at the time it occurs.&nbsp; This entanglement can happen while in flight between planets or systems, or on the way to or from a job.</p>","_id":"yVlyH8pgNclpbi33"}
